result.execSummary:
The defendant Theodore S. Gans was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of THC (2nd+ Offense), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 10:34 a.m. Defendant Theodore S. Gans in court, in custody.  Mary Margaret Sowinski, Asst. DA, appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Calling 14CM273, 14FO645, 16CF105, 15CF155, 16CF157, 16CF299. Court statement. Gans statement--Atty. Cana Kohn no longer counsel as she has taken a new position; public defender will be appointing counsel. Per JA, public defender's office is looking for counsel, but no one assigned at this time. Court notes time limits were waived for preliminary hearing in 16CF299. Sowinski statement--Gans in custody on another case. Court finds cause to extend time for preliminary hearing. 10:38 a.m. adj.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for February 2, 2017 at 01:30 pm.

11:34 a.m. Defendant Theodore S. Gans in court with attorney Cana G Kohn.  Mary Margaret Sowinski appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Calling 16cf157, 15cf155 and 14cm273. Sowinski/Kohn statement-request one additional pre-trial. Bail continued. Defendant questions fine review status - Court sets all financial obligation cases to 1/03/2017. Adj. 11:37 a.m.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for January 3, 2017 at 10:30 am.

3:30 p.m. Defendant Theodore S. Gans in court with attorney Cana G Kohn.  Defendant Theodore S. Gans in custody.  Mary Sowinski appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Calling 16cf157 (Preliminary hearing) 15cf155 (motion to rescind) and 14cm472, 14fo645 (fine reviews) and 14cm273 (dpa review).   In 16cf157 Defendant waives preliminary hearing. Waiver free and voluntary. Court finds that probable cause exists and binds over. State files Information. Kohn - In receipt of Information - waive further reading - not guilty pleas. Bail continued. In 15cf155, Sowinski requests all open cases be consolidated - Court does not allow consolidation but if all cases are part of global resolution cases can be heard by one judge. Court enters judgment in 15cf155; finds defendant guilty of Count 1 and puts over for sentencing to October 4, 2016 in Branch 2. All cases to be tracking with 16cf157 until resolution is determined. Bail continued. Adj. 3:39 p.m.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for October 4, 2016 at 03:00 pm.

2:42 p.m. Defendant Theodore S. Gans in court via video in custody with attorney Mary L. Roth Burns.  Jillian Pfeifer appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  In receipt of complaint, waive reading - Burns moves to modify bond - Pfeifer statement on bond. Court modifies bond to $250 cash bond. Set for preliminary hearing - Time limits waived
Bail continued.
Court notes that 14cm273 is scheduled for review at 3:00 today; 14fo645, 15CF155 and 14cm472 are scheduled for review at 3:30 today. Cases will not be called today. All cases to be set for review on August 10, 2016 at 03:00 p.m. Preliminary hearing scheduled for August 10, 2016 at 03:00 pm.

01:51 pm - Defendant Theodore S. Gans in court with attorney Mary Margaret Hogan.  Defendant Theodore S. Gans in custody.  Jodie L. Bednar appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Calling 15cf155, 14cm431, 14cm273,14cm473, 14cm427, 15cf09, 14cm472 and 15ct16.  In case 15cf155.  State files Information, Hogan in receipt of Information, waive reading and waive preliminary hearing.  In case 14cm273 - State will not rescind DPA at this time.  State moves to dismiss 14cm431, 14cm427, 15cf09 and 15ct16 - Granted.  In case 15cf155 - State moves to amend count 2 to misdemeanor bail jumping - 946.49(1)(a) - Granted.  Defendant pleads no contest to both counts in this case.  In case 14cm473 - Defendant pleads no contest.  In case 14cm472 - State moves to dismiss count 2 - Granted.  Defendant pleads no contest to Count 1.  Plea questionnaire and DPA for Count 1 in 15cf155 filed.    Court reads on waiver of rights and tendering plea. Waiver free and voluntary. Court finds that a factual basis for the plea exists and finds defendant guilty of count 2 in case 15cf155, 14cm473 and count 1 in 14cm472 but defers judgment on count 1 in case 15cf155.  Bednar/Hogan/Defendant/Court statement to sentencing.  Joint recommendation to modify bond in case 15cf155 to a $1500 sig bond - same conditions.    The court informs defendant of right to request expungement of the DNA under Wis. Stat. 165.77(4).
